<br>
I'll never forget my utter amazement as I left highpass hold and was entering the plains of Karana.... I was astounded by how high that mountain pass was.  Just looking down that cliff to the ground so far below was so frightening <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Descending that pass from High Hold to East karana for the first time is one of my favorite EQ memories.<br>
<br>
I hope your death in Oasis hasn't soured you from making this journey.  There is plenty of time to find the good hunting spots later... (I am a big fan of the area around Freeport) But for now enjoy the wonderment of discovering the world and making a truly epic trek across the lands.  (And bind frequently so you don't need to cover the same ground over and over!) <p><table border="0" width="568">
