<br>
Oh, no, it hasn't. I had a lot of fun.  I didn't have much time online yesterday (because I was waiting forever for my Luclin and Velous disks to patch after loading) so I didn't start back yet.  I decided just to explore more of my own continent yesterday.  I went to Lesser Faydark and the Steamboat (Steamfront?) mountains and got to the Gnome city.    I am going to start off again soon though.  I am seeing more and more new creatures in every zone.  I want to go back to the Butcherblock mountains again and spend some time killing Green Bloods too.  LOL, they crack me up when they fall over (I always LMAO at the Aborean Sprouts when they fall as well). <p><center><img src="http://www.boomspeed.com/apothokeri/DraccaSig.gif"><br><br><b><font face="garamond" size=3><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=543802">My Magelo Profile</a></center><font size=0 font face=garamond font color=black></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vilephire>Vilephire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 157<br> <font color=#333333>(1/13/03 7:55:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Well...I took your advice and started off to Qeynos!</span><hr size=1> You are definetely having one of the best EQ experiences you will ever have by enjoying the game in the manner that you are. There are loads of great things to do over the next 4 expansions, but nothing ever has came close to thrill associated with the unknown things during your first few weeks. The terror associated with falling off a boat in the dark, finding a see invis monster blocking my path, and other low level adventures are still some of my most cherished EQ memories. G'Luck in your adventures <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.mfpd.net/bgreer/vilephire.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
