</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=barmodius>Barmodius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#333333>(1/14/03 3:47:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=44>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Well...I took your advice and started off to Qeynos!</span><hr size=1> A great walk down memory lane.  I only started this past October (now lvl 39), and I already miss the good ol' days.<br>
<br>
My first journey across Antonica was 5 minutes after dinging 12, only I went the opposite direction to hunt the ellusive &quot;Sirens&quot; in the Ocean of Tears.  As an Erudite, I boarded the boat at lvl 1 for Qeynos, bound and fought there.  It is still my &quot;home&quot; city, and I still go back frequently to drop some summoned goodies in the newbie area.<br>
<br>
Best thing to do is take your time.  Keep invis up and watch your messages, but do some exploring at the same time.  Most of the mobs between Freeport and Qeynos don't see invis (except undead), so you will be fine.  I spent a great deal of time in West Karana.  The zone is just huge, and has just about everything to see and experience.  I remember the rush of seeing the first Hill Giant, just bouncing across the plain. <br>
<br>
There was one bad experience in the whole trip...Kithicor Forest.  <br>
(storytime)<br>
As one not educated about Kithicor, except not to go at night, I really had no clue.  So I zone in from High Pass (invis), bind at the entrance, check the time (10am), and merrily start down the path. It was kind of cool, because there was a huge group of people at the tunnel.  It was the first time I had seen &quot;a guild&quot;.  I stopped to watch as they merrily played and bonked each other on the head and danced around.  After a minute or two, I resumed down the path.  There were a couple of creatures that were green to me around, so I was not very worried.<br>
<br>
BAM!!  You have been killed by a T'ier Dal something.  Loading, Please wait...back at entrance.  Well, I had been killed in one hit by something nasty that sees through invis.  Now I am naked and need to get my corpse.  I invis again, and not so merrily go down the path.  When I can just barely see my body, I start looking around very wearily.  I slowly creep up to /corpse range, and snag it.  Then I run back to a stone marker and start to loot.<br>
<br>
BAM!!  You have been killed by a T'ier Dal something's pet.  Loading, Please wait...back at entrance.  NOT AGAIN!!   Now I have 2 corpses with 1/2 my equipment distributed between them.  Time to go again.  I go to the end of the tunnel, and the guild is fighting something.  About 5 little blue elves.  they con red to me, but so does everything else.  Well, this one little blue elf is kicking the crap out of a Troll and an Ogre that seem to have pretty good armor.  Both of them die in front of my eyes.  Suddenly, the whole guild rushes towards me and the tunnel.  I see a /shout message &quot;General to HH Zone.  RUN!!&quot;  I turn to run.<br>
<br>
BAM!!  You have been killed by a T'ier Dal something.  Loading, Please wait...back at entrance.  The little blue elves are still there, but I manage to zone to HH before getting hit.  On the other side, the guild is lining the wall and cursing.  They tell me and about 4 other newbies to wait for a little bit, and they will give the OK.  I sit down and wait.  I am now lvl 11, I have no food or drink (too flustered to summon more), and I have 3 corpses lining Kithicor Forest's floor.<br>
<br>
One of the other newbies tells me &quot;Rough time, eh?&quot;  I say yes, and she proceeds to tell me that there is a trick to Kithicor...hug the wall.  Invis, get a SoW, and hug the north wall as far as it will go.  Well, during our wait, some people in the guild give me something called Clarity 2, SoW, and about 7 other buff slot items.  When the all clear is given, I zone back to Kithicor.  I loot my body at the entrance, then run down to the other two.  I drag both of them back to the entrance, and loot them there.  All better, so I hug the North wall and run.  No problems.  Run all the way to the Commonland tunnel without a single problem.  I hunted a bit in WC to get back to lvl 12, then bound as soon as possible.  <br>
(/storytime)<br>
<br>
The rest was pretty boring.  Qeynos area is much more picturesque than the Freeport area.  Green, hilly, with lots of trees.  The commonlands and Freeport are brown and blah.<br>
<br>
I have one suggestion if you feel like exploring...Take a side trip to South Karana.  Stay invis and watch out for undead, but SK is just cool because of all the new types of creatures and scenery.  Centaurs, Elephants, Cyclops, Aviaks, Treants.  Just a cool zone to see, and in your 20s it is a good zone to hunt.  KFC (the nickname of the Aviak city) is a sight to see.<br>
<br>
Good luck in your journeys.  May your trek through Kithicor be a better experience than mine.<br>
<br>
